"BeReal" is an underdiscussed ZOG project, even Joe Biden's PR team had him use it publicly. An app that chooses a random 2 minute period daily when everyone has to take a pic, for the sake of "authenticity". Obviously this is the NWO dream, total control through passive presence

"BeReal" obviously failed as every gimmick does, but it's noteworthy that it existed as pure reaction to true social media culture. In some ways it's the endgame to the Millennial "just log off and enjoy fucking life for a minute" line of thought. Absence occupies time too.

I think "BeReal" was their social media equivalent of Esperanto. They have always despised the non-induced early culture of social media with unreconstructed superiority, health, vulgar wealth displays. E.g. nordids taking Alps vacation pics. We defused another impotent bullet.

Apparently one of the developers is literally a French fed. Having Biden use it is insane. But it's such a good topic to contemplate. They re-conceptualize "spontaneousness" to mean responding to unexpected given stimuli: basically MK-Ultra-ish being given random electric shocks.

It re-defines authenticity as "lack of free will". The way you choose to naturally express and present yourself online is "fake", but being forced to respond to an almost militaristic command is "genuine", "who you really are". In the end, you get military dog training for humans

I genuinely believe "BeReal" held Mankind-Enslavement Project potential. Billions rushing to obediently take a selfie at their office when the daily notification hits, wondering when it will ring out throughout the day, ears wide open. Death of freedom. Hell. ZOG.
